---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  pageType="guide"
  guideTopic="permits"
  title="Do You Need a Permit for a Shipping Container? | Steel Box Direct"
  description="Understand when permits are needed for shipping containers. Common scenarios for residential, agricultural, and commercial properties."
>
  <div class="guide-header" style="background: var(--c5-permits); color: var(--cream);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sh" style="border-color: var(--cream);">
        <span class="idx">§ 05</span>
        <span class="nm" style="color: var(--cream);">Decision: Permits</span>
        <span class="tg" style="color: var(--cream);">Zoning & Land Use</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="big" style="color: var(--cream);">Do I need<br><em>A permit?</em></h1>
      <p class="guide-lede" style="opacity: .9;">
        Usually no. Most farm storage is zoned-exempt in OH, IN, and KY. If you're residential or commercial,
        we'll tell you how to check without the headache.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="guide-content">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="main-col">
          <h2>Agricultural and Rural Properties</h2>
          <p>Rural properties typically have the most flexibility. Agricultural exemptions are the standard for equipment storage.</p>

          <div class="permit-card" style="border-left-color: var(--c4-cost);">
            <h3>Likely NO Permit Required</h3>
            <div class="m" style="color: var(--c4-cost); margin-bottom: 12px;">Ag-Exempt Status</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Equipment storage:</strong> Tractors, implements, grain drills.</li>
              <li><strong>Agricultural materials:</strong> Feed, tools, seasonal supplies.</li>
              <li><strong>Temporary placement:</strong> Sitting on ground, not a foundation.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="who">→ Tom · Equipment Farmer</div>
          </div>

          <div class="permit-card" style="border-left-color: var(--c2-cond);">
            <h3>When You Might Need One</h3>
            <div class="m" style="color: var(--c2-cond); margin-bottom: 12px;">Standard Restrictions</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Habitable space:</strong> Conversion to office or living quarters.</li>
              <li><strong>Property lines:</strong> Placement within 10-20ft of a boundary.</li>
              <li><strong>City Limits:</strong> Properties within incorporated town boundaries.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="sidebar-col">
          <div class="authority-card">
            <div class="m">Zoning Facts</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>73%</strong> of rural properties require no storage permits.</li>
              <li><strong>Farm use</strong> is the most common path to exemption.</li>
              <li><strong>Unincorporated</strong> land has minimal zoning oversight.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="cta-card">
            <h4>Check your area</h4>
            <p>We'll flag any known local restrictions during your quote call.</p>
            <a href="/quote/" class="btn">Get a Quote <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg></a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .guide-header {
      padding: 80px 0 64px;
      border-bottom: 2.5px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .guide-lede {
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.45;
      margin: 40px 0 0;
      max-width: 720px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .guide-content {
      padding: 96px 0;
      background: var(--cream);
    }

    .row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
      gap: 80px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .permit-card {
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      border-left: 8px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      margin-top: 40px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--ink);
    }
    .permit-card h3 {
      font-family: var(--narrow);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 28px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .permit-card ul {
      margin: 20px 0 0;
      padding: 0;
      list-style: none;
    }
    .permit-card li {
      padding: 8px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(11,15,26,.1);
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.45;
    }
    .permit-card li:last-child { border: none; }
    
    .who {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: .08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 4px 8px;
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--cream);
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 24px;
    }

    .authority-card {
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--cream);
      padding: 32px;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .authority-card .m { color: var(--yellow); margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .authority-card li { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.45; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(246,241,231,.1); padding-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card li:last-child { border: none; }

    .cta-card {
      margin-top: 40px;
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--c5-permits);
    }
    .cta-card h4 { font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: 24px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .cta-card p { font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 48px; }
      .guide-header { padding: 48px 0; }
      .big { font-size: clamp(48px, 10vw, 80px); }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>